  "prompt": "Are patents valuable to tech startups?",
  "response": "Patents can be valuable to tech startups in several ways:\n\n1. Competitive Advantages\n- Provides legal protection for unique technologies\n- Prevents competitors from copying core innovations\n- Establishes intellectual property rights\n\n2. Potential Financial Benefits\n- Can be licensed to generate revenue\n- Increases company valuation\n- Attractive to investors during funding rounds\n\n3. Strategic Considerations\n- Demonstrates technical innovation\n- Can serve as defensive protection against patent lawsuits\n- Signals technical credibility to investors and partners\n\n4. Potential Drawbacks\n- High filing and maintenance costs\n- Patent process can be time-consuming\n- May limit some future technological flexibility\n\n5. Situational Value\n- More valuable in certain tech sectors (biotech, hardware)\n- Less critical in rapidly evolving software domains\n- Depends on specific technology and market dynamics\n\nOverall, patents can be valuable but aren't universally essential. Their worth depends on the startup's specific technology, industry, and business strategy.",
